        "question": "<p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"> <span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Which of the following statements is/are correct regarding the regional features of Gujarat’s medieval architecture?</b></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Architectural forms in Gujarat often incorporated elements from local temple traditions.</b></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Structures such as mosques and tombs in Gujarat featured ornamental carvings like toranas and bell motifs.</b></span></span></span></span></p> <p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Gujarat’s architectural style strictly avoided any decorative influence from indigenous practices.</b></span></span></span></span></p>",
